A Function That Exports Tables and/or SEM Digrams based on dySEM models

outputModel.Rd

This function takes the model from fitted dySEM() scripts and exports table(s) and/or a path diagram figure of expected output.

outputModel(
  dvn,
  model = NULL,
  fit,
  table = TRUE,
  tabletype = NULL,
  figure = TRUE,
  figtype = NULL
)

Arguments

dvn

input dvn list from scrapeVarCross
model

character input specying type of model to output (e.g., "cfa", "apim", "cfm")
fit

input object from fitted lavaan model
table

logical input of whether table output is desired. Default is TRUE
tabletype

character input of what type of table(s) is(are) desired. options are "measurement" (i.e,, loadings, intercepts,), "structural" (i.e., latent slopes, such as actor/partner effects, k parameters), or "both" (i.e., both measurement and structural tables)
figure

logical input of whether figure output is desired. Default is TRUE
figtype

character input of what type of figure is desired.

Value

Ignore console (prints unneccessary semPlot::semPaths details). More importantly, prints word files for the table(s) and/or figure, outputed to the users working directory

Examples

dvnx <- scrapeVarCross(dat = commitmentQ, x_order = "spi", x_stem = "sat.g", x_delim1 = ".", x_delim2="_", distinguish_1="1", distinguish_2="2")
sat.config.script <-  scriptCFA(dvnx, lvname = "Sat", model = "configural")
sat.config.mod <- cfa(sat.config.script, data = commitmentQ, std.lv = F, auto.fix.first= F, meanstructure = T)

#> Error in cfa(sat.config.script, data = commitmentQ, std.lv = F, auto.fix.first = F,     meanstructure = T): could not find function "cfa"
outputModel(dvnx, model = "cfa", fit = sat.config.mod, table = TRUE, tabletype = "measurement", figure = "TRUE", figtype = "standardized")

#> Error in lavaan::parameterEstimates(fit, standardized = TRUE): object 'sat.config.mod' not found
dvnxy <- scrapeVarCross(dat = commitmentQ, x_order = "spi", x_stem = "sat.g", x_delim1 = ".", x_delim2="_", distinguish_1="1", distinguish_2="2",
y_order="spi", y_stem="com", y_delim1 = ".", y_delim2="_")
apim.script.config <-  scriptAPIM(dvnxy, lvxname = "Sat", lvyname = "Com", model = "configural")
apim.config.fit <- cfa(apim.script.config, data = commitmentQ, std.lv = F, auto.fix.first= F, meanstructure = T)

#> Error in cfa(apim.script.config, data = commitmentQ, std.lv = F, auto.fix.first = F,     meanstructure = T): could not find function "cfa"
outputModel(dvnxy, model = "apim", fit = apim.config.fit, table = TRUE, tabletype = "measurement", figure = "TRUE", figtype = "standardized")

#> Error in lavaan::parameterEstimates(fit, standardized = TRUE): object 'apim.config.fit' not found
